title: The Top 10 Hip Hop Singles & Videos Of The Week: The Notorious B.I.G., Uncle Murda & Dave East
text:
This week, Justin Hunte explains why The Notorious B.I.G. shouldn’t be considered the GOAT. Elsewhere, Uncle Murda does a recap of rap’s craziest moments in 2016 and Dave East makes an appearance on BET’s Being Mary Jane. Biggie Is NOT The GOAT 
In this week’s Breakdown, Justin Hunte gives a compelling argument about why Biggie can’t be the GOAT . The notion has ruffled feathers on social media with some agreeing, thanking him for saying what many were already thinking while others still hold Christopher Wallace as their favorite MC. 
Check out the argument on The Breakdown below. Uncle Murda Goes Over Rap In 2016 
Uncle Murda cleverly delivers a recap of 2016’s craziest moments with his “Rap Up 2016″ freestyle, over production from Reefa and Teddy Da Don. He touches on Meek Mill/The Game’s beef, Troy Ave’s shooting, Kanye West’s hospitalization, Donald Trump’s victory and Gucci Mane’s release from prison. Dave East Stars In “Being Mary Jane” 
Dave East stars in the premiere episode of Being Mary Jane, which begins on January 10 at 9P/8C on BET. Mary Jane Paul, played by Gabrielle Union, starts a new gig in NYC on Great Day USA and gets to interview East for his first assignment. He even performs a cut off 2015’s Hate Me Now , called “KD.”
